<treatmentCitation id="AC1C10B4C0764B14FF214831FD22316C" author="Schenkling S." box="[224,661,1379,1403]" page="288" pageId="23" pageNumber="22" year="1900">
<taxonomicName id="EABD4D26C0764B14FF214831FD22316C" authority="Schenkling, 1900: 288" authorityName="Schenkling" authorityPageNumber="288" authorityYear="1900" box="[224,661,1379,1403]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Axina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="centrimaculata">
<emphasis id="1FC9EAB7C0764B14FF214831FE01316C" box="[224,438,1379,1403]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Axina centrimaculata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="492C4B54C0764B14FE784836FD22316C" author="Schenkling S." box="[441,661,1379,1403]" pageId="23" pageNumber="22" pagination="385 - 409" refId="ref45418" refString="Schenkling S. 1900. Neue amerikanische Cleriden nebst Bemerkungen zu schon Beschriebenen Arten. Deutschen Entomologische Zeitschrift 1900: 385 - 409." type="journal article" year="1900">Schenkling, 1900: 288</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</treatmentCitation>
. 
<emphasis id="1FC9EAB7C0764B14FD5C4836FCB2316C" bold="true" box="[669,773,1379,1403]" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">
<typeStatus id="F2068807C0764B14FD5C4836FCB2316C" box="[669,773,1379,1403]" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Lectotype</typeStatus>
</emphasis>
. Female. 
<emphasis id="1FC9EAB7C0764B14FCA04836FBA7316C" bold="true" box="[865,1040,1379,1403]" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Here designated.</emphasis>
Type locality: Goyaz, Brasilia, Donckier (SDEI). 
<treatmentCitation id="AC1C10B4C0764B14FE9048D7FDA1318C" author="Corporaal JB" box="[337,534,1410,1435]" page="98" pageId="23" pageNumber="22" year="1950">
<bibRefCitation id="492C4B54C0764B14FE9048D7FDA1318C" author="Corporaal JB" box="[337,534,1410,1435]" pageId="23" pageNumber="22" refId="ref44328" refString="Corporaal JB. 1950. Cleridae. In: Hinks WD (ed.). Coleopterorum catalogus supplementa, Pars 23 (editio secunda). W. Junk; Gravenhage, The Netherlands. 373 p." type="book" year="1950">Corporaal 1950: 98</bibRefCitation>
</treatmentCitation>
. There is indication that Schenkling examined more than one specimen in his description of this species, but he did not select a 
<typeStatus id="F2068807C0764B14FDB848F7FD6331AD" box="[633,724,1442,1466]" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">holotype</typeStatus>
, therefore, I invoke Recommendation 73F of the 
<bibRefCitation id="492C4B54C0764B14FB0048F7FAF331AD" author="ICZN &amp; International Code of Zoological Nomenclature" box="[1217,1348,1442,1466]" pageId="23" pageNumber="22" refId="ref44854" refString="(ICZN) International Code of Zoological Nomenclature. 1999. 4 th Edition. Adopted by the International Union of Biological Sciences. The International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature; London, United Kingdom. 306 p." type="book" year="1999">ICZN (1999)</bibRefCitation>
and designate a 
<typeStatus id="F2068807C0764B14FE954894FE0731CE" box="[340,432,1473,1497]" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">lectotype</typeStatus>
for this nominal species.
</treatmentCitationGroup>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="65A7652EC0764B14FF0148BCFD2E327B" pageId="23" pageNumber="22" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="2D0236A5C0764B14FF0148BCFD2E327B" blockId="23.[192,1440,1512,1644]" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis id="1FC9EAB7C0764B14FF0148BCFE8B3214" bold="true" box="[192,316,1513,1539]" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Its comparatively small size (length about 
<quantity id="EA459B40C0764B14FCE548BCFCDD3213" box="[804,874,1513,1540]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="23" pageNumber="22" unit="mm" value="6.0">6 mm</quantity>
), the round testaceous marking on the basal ½ of the elytral disc along with the broad obliquely positioned macula behind the middle of the elytral disc are characteristics that will distinguish the members of this species from superficially similar and larger (about 
<quantity id="EA459B40C0764B14FA874B7BFA2F325E" box="[1350,1432,1582,1609]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="23" pageNumber="22" unit="mm" value="11.0">11 mm</quantity>
) specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="EABD4D26C0764B14FE964B04FD22327B" authority="(Chevrolat)" baseAuthorityName="Chevrolat" box="[343,661,1617,1644]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Axina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bifasciata">
<emphasis id="1FC9EAB7C0764B14FE964B04FDBD327C" box="[343,522,1617,1643]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Axina bifasciata</emphasis>
(Chevrolat)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="65A7652EC0764B1BFF014B2EFD013549" lastPageId="24" lastPageNumber="23" pageId="23" pageNumber="22" type="description">
<paragraph id="2D0236A5C0764B1BFF014B2EFE013505" blockId="23.[191,1441,1659,1927]" lastBlockId="24.[192,1439,214,274]" lastPageId="24" lastPageNumber="23" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis id="1FC9EAB7C0764B14FF014B2EFEDC3282" bold="true" box="[192,363,1659,1685]" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Redescription.</emphasis>
<emphasis id="1FC9EAB7C0764B14FEB24B29FE293281" box="[371,414,1660,1686]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Size</emphasis>
. Length 6.0 mm; width 
<quantity id="EA459B40C0764B14FD754B2EFCB83281" box="[692,783,1659,1686]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="23" pageNumber="22" unit="mm" value="1.5">1.5 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis id="1FC9EAB7C0764B14FCDD4B29FCE23282" box="[796,853,1660,1685]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Form</emphasis>
. As in 
<figureCitation id="B5862A20C0764B14FC684B2EFC4E3282" box="[937,1017,1659,1685]" captionStart="Figures 90–93" captionStartId="63.[192,279,1859,1885]" captionTargetBox="[192,1304,213,1828]" captionTargetId="figure-10@63.[192,1304,213,1828]" captionTargetPageId="63" captionText="Figures 90–93. Habitus of Axina species. 90) Axina latilinea. 91) A. phallospina. 92) A. apicalis. 93) A. centrimaculata." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4565017" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4565017/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Fig. 93</figureCitation>
. 
<emphasis id="1FC9EAB7C0764B14FBC44B2EFBF53282" box="[1029,1090,1659,1685]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Color</emphasis>
. Cranium castaneous; antenna testaceous; prothorax bicolorous, venter testaceous, pronotal sides dark castaneous, pronotal middle light castaneous; elytra bicolorous, disc mostly castaneous, large round testaceous marking in elytral basal ½, each elytron with wide obliquely position macula behind middle, and apical 1⁄5 
<superScript id="DAC89BEDC0764B14FC544BB7FC1432E7" attach="left" box="[917,931,1762,1776]" fontSize="6" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">th</superScript>
testaceous; legs bicolorous, distal ½ of femora and proximal ½ of tibiae dark brown, remainder of legs testaceous; abdomen flavotestaceous. 
<emphasis id="1FC9EAB7C0764B14FB304A50FA9B3308" box="[1265,1324,1797,1823]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Head</emphasis>
. Cranium finely punctate, frons wider than length of antennal pedicel; EW/FW 33/15. 
<emphasis id="1FC9EAB7C0764B14FBDF4A72FBDC3356" box="[1054,1131,1831,1857]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Thorax</emphasis>
. Pronotum finely punctate, with 2 tumescences, narrowly concave at middle; PW/PL 67/90; elytra with asetiferous punctures substriate, punctures extend slightly beyond elytron middle, width of interstitial spaces varies; EL/EW 150/50. 
<emphasis id="1FC9EAB7C0764B14FAF34A39FA2D3391" box="[1330,1434,1900,1926]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Abdomen</emphasis>
. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="B5862A20C0794B1BFEFA4D83FE3C34E7" box="[315,395,214,240]" captionStart="Figures 44–49" captionStartId="50.[192,279,1818,1844]" captionTargetBox="[320,1267,1056,1788]" captionTargetId="figure-38@50.[320,1267,1056,1788]" captionText="Figures 44–49. Aedeagi. 44) Axina chiasta. 45) A. conspicua. 46) A. fasciata. 47) A. centrimaculata. 48) A. fortipes. 49) A. furcula." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4586061" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4586061/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">Fig. 47</figureCitation>
), phallobasic lobes very short, contiguous; edge of phallic plates minutely serrate; phallobasic apodeme abbreviated.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2D0236A5C0794B1BFF014C77FD013549" blockId="24.[192,1440,289,350]" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis id="1FC9EAB7C0794B1BFF014C77FF48352B" bold="true" box="[192,255,290,316]" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">Note.</emphasis>
Previously 
<taxonomicName id="EABD4D26C0794B1BFE404C77FDF2352C" box="[385,581,289,316]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Axina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="centrimaculata">
<emphasis id="1FC9EAB7C0794B1BFE404C77FE24352B" box="[385,403,290,316]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="1FC9EAB7C0794B1BFE614C74FDF2352C" box="[416,581,289,315]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">centrimaculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was considered a synony of 
<taxonomicName id="EABD4D26C0794B1BFC434C74FB77352B" authority="(Chevrolat)" baseAuthorityName="Chevrolat" box="[898,1216,289,316]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Axina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bifasciata">Axina bifasciata (Chevrolat)</taxonomicName>
. I consider it a valid species and here revalidate the species status.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="65A7652EC0794B1BFF014C38FEA835DB" pageId="24" pageNumber="23" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="2D0236A5C0794B1BFF014C38FEA835DB" blockId="24.[192,1440,365,460]" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis id="1FC9EAB7C0794B1BFF014C38FEE43590" bold="true" box="[192,339,365,391]" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">Distribution</emphasis>
(for map see 
<figureCitation id="B5862A20C0794B1BFE2C4C38FD8C359F" box="[493,571,365,392]" captionStart="Figure 70" captionStartId="55.[192,268,1865,1891]" captionTargetBox="[192,1440,213,1820]" captionTargetId="figure-10@55.[192,1440,213,1828]" captionTargetPageId="55" captionText="Figure 70. Distribution map for Axina species: A. macilenta, A. oligocheia, A. parcepunctata, A. schenklingi, A. basalis, A. latilinea, A. phallospina, A. apicalis, A. centrimaculata, A. fasciata, A. heveli, A. klisis, A. lateralis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4565001" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4565001/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">Fig. 70</figureCitation>
). In addition to the 
<typeStatus id="F2068807C0794B1BFCDC4C38FC323590" box="[797,901,365,391]" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">lectotype</typeStatus>
, I examined one specimen from: 
<emphasis id="1FC9EAB7C0794B1BFB3D4C38FE3735BE" bold="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">
<collectingCountry id="55AA7635C0794B1BFB3D4C38FAF23590" box="[1276,1349,365,391]" name="Brazil" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">Brazil</collectingCountry>
: Estado do 
<collectingRegion id="EF79F847C0794B1BFF264CDAFE3735BE" box="[231,384,399,425]" country="Brazil" name="Mato Grosso" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">Mato Grosso</collectingRegion>
</emphasis>
, Corumba, collection day and collector not noted. Specimens are deposited in: FMNH and MNHN.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
